    text: '<p class="RuleNumber-GameRulesRobot"><a name="_Ref88308684"></a><a name="G106"></a><b><span style="color:#1E5AA8">G106</span></b><b><span style="font-size:7.0pt;\nline-height:106%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;color:#1E5AA8">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span><span class="Headline">Tall </span><span class="GlossaryTerm-Headline">Robots</span><span class="Headline"> in </span><span class="GlossaryTerm-Headline">Hangar Zone</span><span class="Headline"> only.</span></b> <span class="GlossaryTerm">Robot</span> height,\nas measured when it’s resting normally on a flat floor, may not exceed the\nmaximum <span class="GlossaryTerm">Starting Configuration</span> height (4 ft. 4\nin. (~132 cm)) unless any part of the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Robot’s</span><span class="Normal-char"> </span><span class="GlossaryTerm">Bumpers</span> is in its <span class="GlossaryTerm">Hangar Zone,</span> in which case its height may not exceed\n5 ft. 6 in. (~167 cm).</p><p class="Violation">Violation: <span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>Foul</i></span>. <span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>Tech Foul</i></span> if the over-extension blocks an\nopponent’s shot, scores a <span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>Cargo</i></span>, or is\nthe first thing that contacts <span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>Cargo</i></span>\nexiting from an <span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>Upper Exit</i></span>. If the\nover-extension enables <span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>Hangar</i></span> points,\nthe <span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>Robot</i></span> is no longer eligible for <span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>Hangar</i></span> points. </p><div style="border:solid #0DBDD4 1.5pt;padding:0in 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\nmargin-left:.75in;margin-right:.75in">\n\n<p class="BlueBox" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\nmargin-left:0in"><span style="color:black">This measurement is intended to be\nmade as if the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Robot</span> is resting on a flat\nfloor, not relative to the height of the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Robot</span>\nfrom the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Field</span> carpet. </span></p>\n\n<p class="BlueBox" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\nmargin-left:0in"><span style="color:black">For example, a <span class="GlossaryTerm">Robot</span> that is at an angle while driving over\nsomething may actually exceed the height limit when compared to the carpet of\nthe <span class="GlossaryTerm">Field</span>.</span></p>\n\n<p class="BlueBox-Caption" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\n6.0pt;margin-left:0in">&nbsp;Figure 7‑1 <span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>Robot</i></span>\nheight example</p>\n\n<p class="BlueBox" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\nmargin-left:0in"><span style="color:black;mso-color-alt:windowtext"><span style="mso-no-proof:yes"><img border="0" width="480" height="194" id="_x0000_i1063" src="https://firstfrc.blob.core.windows.net/frc2022/Manual/HTML/2022FRCGameManual_files/image049.png" alt="Two robots of legal height. One is standing normally on a flat floor. The other robot is tilted. Checks indicate that both robots are okay."></span></span></p>\n\n</div>',
