    text: '<p class="RuleNumber-GameRulesRobots-Evergreen"><a name="_Ref85540158"></a><a name="G206"></a><span class="Headline"><span style="color:#3C7B3B">G206</span></span><span class="Headline"><span style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:106%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;\ncolor:#3C7B3B">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span class="Headline-Evergreen">*Don’t tip or entangle.</span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:windowtext;font-weight:normal"> A </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm">robot</span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:windowtext;\nfont-weight:normal"> may not deliberately, as perceived by a </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm">referee</span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:windowtext;\nfont-weight:normal">, attach to, tip, or entangle with an opponent </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm">robot</span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:windowtext;\nfont-weight:normal">. </span></span></p><p class="Violation"><span class="Headline"><span style="color:gray;font-weight:\nnormal">Violation: </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>Tech foul</i></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:gray;font-weight:normal"> and </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>yellow card</i></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:gray;font-weight:normal">. If </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>continuous</i></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:gray;font-weight:normal"> or opponent </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>robot</i></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:gray;font-weight:normal"> is unable to drive, </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>Tech</i></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:gray;font-weight:normal"> </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>foul</i></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:gray;font-weight:normal"> and </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>red</i></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:gray;font-weight:normal"> </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>card</i></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:gray;font-weight:normal">. </span></span></p><div style="border:solid #0DBDD4 1.5pt;padding:0in 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\nmargin-left:.75in;margin-right:.75in">\n\n<p class="BlueBox" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\nmargin-left:0in"><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;font-weight:\nnormal">Examples of violations of this rule include, but are not limited to:</span></span></p>\n\n<p class="BlueBox-LetteredList" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;\nmargin-bottom:6.0pt;margin-left:.25in"><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;mso-color-alt:windowtext;font-weight:normal">a.</span></span><span class="Headline"><span style="font-size:7.0pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;\ncolor:black;mso-color-alt:windowtext;font-weight:normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;font-weight:normal">using\na wedge-like </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><span style="color:black">mechanism</span></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;font-weight:normal"> to tip over\nopponent </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><span style="color:black">robots,</span></span></p>\n\n<p class="BlueBox-LetteredList" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;\nmargin-bottom:6.0pt;margin-left:.25in"><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;mso-color-alt:windowtext;font-weight:normal">b.</span></span><span class="Headline"><span style="font-size:7.0pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;\ncolor:black;mso-color-alt:windowtext;font-weight:normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;font-weight:normal">making\n</span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><span style="color:black">bumper</span></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;font-weight:normal">-to-</span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><span style="color:black">bumper</span></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;font-weight:normal"> contact with an\nopponent </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><span style="color:black">robot</span></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;font-weight:normal"> that is attempting\nto right itself after previously falling over and causing them to fall over\nagain, and </span></span></p>\n\n<p class="BlueBox-LetteredList" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;\nmargin-bottom:6.0pt;margin-left:.25in"><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;mso-color-alt:windowtext;font-weight:normal">c.</span></span><span class="Headline"><span style="font-size:7.0pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;\ncolor:black;mso-color-alt:windowtext;font-weight:normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;font-weight:normal">causing\nan opponent </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><span style="color:black">robot</span></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;font-weight:normal"> to tip over by\ncontacting the </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><span style="color:black">robot</span></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;font-weight:normal"> after it starts to\ntip if, in the judgement of the </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><span style="color:black">referee</span></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;font-weight:normal">, that contact could have been avoided.</span></span></p>\n\n<p class="BlueBox" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\nmargin-left:0in"><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;font-weight:\nnormal">Tipping as an unintended consequence of normal </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><span style="color:black">robot</span></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;font-weight:normal"> to </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><span style="color:black">robot</span></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;font-weight:normal"> interaction, as\nperceived by the </span></span><span class="GlossaryTerm"><span style="color:\nblack">referee</span></span><span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;\nfont-weight:normal">, is not a violation of </span></span><span style="color:black">G206<span class="Headline"><span style="color:black;\nfont-weight:normal">.</span></span></span></p>\n\n</div>',
