    text: '<p class="RuleNumber-GameRulesHumans-Evergreen"><a name="H402"></a><b><span style="color:#3C7B3B">H402</span></b><b><span style="font-size:7.0pt;\nline-height:106%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;color:#3C7B3B">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span><span class="Headline-Evergreen">*Disconnect or set down controllers.</span></b>\nPrior to the start of the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Match,</span> any control\ndevices worn or held by <span class="GlossaryTerm">Human Players</span> and/or <span class="GlossaryTerm">Drivers</span> must be disconnected from the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Operator Console</span>. </p><p class="Violation">Violation: <span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>Match</i></span>\nwon’t start until the situation is corrected. </p><div style="border:solid #0DBDD4 1.5pt;padding:0in 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\nmargin-left:.75in;margin-right:.75in">\n\n<p class="BlueBox" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\nmargin-left:0in"><span style="color:black">For the purposes of <i>FIRST</i> <span class="NormalText">Robotics Competition</span>, any device connected to the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Operator Console</span> is considered a control device\nbecause <span class="GlossaryTerm">Referees</span> are not expected to\ndifferentiate between devices that can or cannot control the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Robot</span>.</span></p>\n\n</div>',
