    text: '<p class="RuleNumber-Robot-Evergreen"><a name="R101"></a><b><span style="color:\n#3C7B3B">R101</span></b><b><span style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:106%;\nfont-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;color:#3C7B3B">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span><span class="Headline-Evergreen">*</span><span class="Headline-EvergreenGlossaryterm">Frame Perimeter</span><span class="Headline-Evergreen"> must be fixed.</span></b> The <span class="GlossaryTerm">Robot</span> (excluding <span class="GlossaryTerm">Bumpers</span>)\nmust have a <span class="GlossaryTerm">Frame Perimeter</span>, contained within\nthe <span class="GlossaryTerm">Bumper Zone</span> and established while in the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Robot’s</span> <span class="GlossaryTerm">Starting\nConfiguration</span>, that is comprised of <a name="FRAMEPERIMETER">fixed, non-articulated\nstructural elements of the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Robot</span></a>. Minor\nprotrusions no greater than ¼ in. (~6 mm) such as bolt heads, fastener ends,\nweld beads, and rivets are not considered part of the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Frame\nPerimeter</span>.</p><div style="border:solid #0DBDD4 1.5pt;padding:0in 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\nmargin-left:.75in;margin-right:.75in">\n\n<p class="BlueBox" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\nmargin-left:0in"><span style="color:black">To determine the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Frame Perimeter</span>, wrap a piece of string around the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Robot</span> (excluding <span class="GlossaryTerm">Bumpers</span>)\nat the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Bumper Zone</span> described in R402 and pull\nit taut. The string outlines the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Frame Perimeter</span>.\n</span></p>\n\n<p class="BlueBox" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\nmargin-left:0in"><span style="color:black">Example: A <span class="GlossaryTerm">Robot’s</span>\nchassis is shaped like the letter ‘V’, with a large gap between chassis\nelements on the front of the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Robot</span>. When\nwrapping a taut string around this chassis, the string extends across the gap\nand the resulting <span class="GlossaryTerm">Frame Perimeter</span> is a triangle\nwith 3 sides.</span></p>\n\n<p class="BBCaption" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\nmargin-left:0in;page-break-after:avoid">Figure 9‑1 FRAME PERIMETER\nexample</p>\n\n<p class="BlueBox" align="center" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;\nmargin-bottom:6.0pt;margin-left:0in;text-align:center;page-break-after:avoid"><span style="color:black;mso-color-alt:windowtext"><span style="mso-no-proof:yes"><img border="0" width="408" height="176" id="_x0000_i1058" src="https://firstfrc.blob.core.windows.net/frc2022/Manual/HTML/2022FRCGameManual_files/image053.png" alt="A V-shaped robot has a triangular frame perimeter."></span></span></p>\n\n</div>',
