    text: '<p class="RuleNumber-Robot-Evergreen"><a name="R410"></a><b><span style="color:\n#3C7B3B">R410</span></b><b><span style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:106%;\nfont-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;color:#3C7B3B">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span><span class="Headline-EvergreenGlossaryterm">*Bumpers</span><span class="Headline-Evergreen"> must be supported.</span></b> <span class="GlossaryTerm">Bumpers</span> must be supported by the structure/frame of\nthe <span class="GlossaryTerm">Robot</span> (see Figure 9‑9). To be\nconsidered supported, a minimum of ½ in. (~13 mm) at each end of each <span class="GlossaryTerm">Bumper</span> wood segment must be backed by the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Frame Perimeter</span> (≤¼ in. gap, ~6mm). “Ends”\nexclude hard <span class="GlossaryTerm">Bumper</span> parts which extend past the\n<span class="GlossaryTerm">Frame Perimeter</span> permitted by R408-B.\nAdditionally, any gap between the backing material and the frame:</p><p class="MsoListParagraph">A.<span style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:106%;\nfont-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>must not\nbe greater than ¼ in. (~6 mm) deep or</p><p class="MsoListParagraph">B.<span style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:106%;\nfont-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>not more\nthan 8 in. (~20 cm) wide</p><p class="MsoCaption" style="page-break-after:auto"><a name="_Ref81469098">Figure\n</a>9‑9 <span class="GlossaryTerm"><i>Bumper</i></span> support examples</p><p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><span style="mso-no-proof:yes"><img border="0" width="338" height="282" id="_x0000_i1050" src="https://firstfrc.blob.core.windows.net/frc2022/Manual/HTML/2022FRCGameManual_files/image061.jpg" alt="A robot with cutouts and bumpers in front of gaps in the frame perimeter labeled OK and NOT OK."></span></p><div style="border:solid #0DBDD4 1.5pt;padding:0in 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\nmargin-left:.75in;margin-right:.75in">\n\n<p class="BlueBox" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\nmargin-left:0in"><span style="color:black">The intent of this rule is to make\nsure the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Bumper</span> wood is properly supported to\nminimize the likelihood of breakage on impact. Flexible <span class="GlossaryTerm">Robot</span> elements, such as thin plastic, do not\naccomplish this intent and are not considered “structure/frame” of the <span class="GlossaryTerm">Robot</span>.</span></p>\n\n</div>',
